I guess I was trying to point out that it is probably more of a continuous
spectrum than a binary attribute. Nature and good alife is one end of the
spectrum, Golem is somewhere in the middle, and matching a complex picture
pixel for pixel is on the other end.

So, if the problems you outline with TBE are right (and I think many of them
are), then it might make sense to say something like &quot;the more you move away
from TBE, the less you will have these problems.&quot;
